          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 9 1/2 in. by 5 5/8, consisting of 143 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 3, 9, 10, 22, 31, 56, 77, 142, and 143. The quires, 15 in number, were originally signed with arithmetical figures (fol. 77 a,% <!-- needs coptic cursive numbers -->) but have since been twice re-numbered with letters, on the second occasion incorrectly. Leaves are wanting after foll. 52, 53, 55, 56, and 94. Each page has from 23 to 28 lines.</p>
